4.24.23  6:35 pm   do you think there is truth to the "you either got it or you don't"?

     it seems like there's hardly enough information in that line to really be useful. it sounds like it's alluding to something else

     i ask because i have been really trying to commit myself to daily songgen sessions and while i am committed to keeping up with this exercise, i still sometimes feel scared that maybe its not worth it because maybe i just "dont have it".

     bizarrely, it's not really gonna be "you" who "has it". ultimately it would be "it" who "has you". i know this seems annoying if you want it really badly, because it's almost impossible to get it to adhere to your time schedule

     i really want this,

     that's exactly the hardest part

     but im just scared the songs i write will never be good enough and that its not bruteforcable

     it definitely is not bruteforceable. but if you really want it, it probably is meant to be. although, ironically, "really wanting it" is not the condition that will produce it. if you find yourself stuck in this 'determined' state, then it might be useful to try writing bad songs on purpose, for now. it can be surprisingly thrilling, and it is a way to access the reverse psychology you need, on demand, instead of having to wait until you "don't" want it
